reviewText: In the tiny world of chopper movies, this one stands out. These are the real people that build the rolling artwork that you see in the magazines.
All around excellent, and if you pay close attention you'll get that extra nugget that's rarely found in other bike documentaries.
Seriously enjoyable madness. Real folks out burning up the asphalt.. No trailer queens. Worth the watch, better yet, getcher butt there next time..
well done, captures the spirit of this event and the culture
Great video to learn about the chopper sub-culture.  if you like the biker lifestyle this is a must see!
the horse is a great mag.a fun look at an event that started small
